Designed alongside other "spetsialnaya" group Soviet era weapons such as the AS Val and the OTs-14 "Groza", in order to replace general use weapons, such as the AK-74.  Ironically enough, the Vintorez also lacks a niche: it can be used in stealth operations, as marksman rifle, as a pseudo-SMG, and as general use "assault weapon".  The only downsides are the relative low effective range and the pronunciated bullet drop, both due the properties of the 9x39mm.
